result.name: 666 Boat Noodle

reviews.text: If you're looking for authentic Thai boat noodles then this is as close as you're going to get in Hong Kong. The price point is also very low that's making it quite affordable. Traditional Thai Boat noodles are a must try along with the curry noodles and the hainanese chicken rice. portion sizes come in regular or large sizes. Regular size is recommended as it allows you to try many different varieties of food.

Interesting deco
Very small portions 
The boat noodles is just average.

Cozy cozy place for thai food.
The interior is amazing and makes you feel like you are in Southeast Asia
The portions are small, maybe a few spoonfuls and you are done but the price reflects the volume as well.

Update: since then, I have visited the place a couple times and have decided to edit my rating and review for the consistently bad service. The waiters are unprofessional and rude the past 3 times I've visited.

This place isn't Samsen (in wanchai) but it's still delicious, and more importantly it's much more affordable. Thai boat noodles will only set you back 25hkd for smaller Thai size, and 38hkd for the larger Hong Kong size. Skewers come at 40hkd per 2 skewers. Hainan chicken rice is 42 for a larger plate. Everything was solid and totally satisfied my craving for some simple Thai fare. Recommended!
Nice Thai noodle soup serving in small and big size. Small plates are good as well with reasonable price. Not much seats but the feel is right.

reviews.text:
非常地道的泰國船麵，也非常貼心，因為傳統船麵份量是比較少，所以會有香港份量選擇。

湯底非常香濃，味道很地道，菜式也非常多。👍👍

推介 ： 扎肉金邊粉，春卷，蝦餅，醃生蝦，沙爹串。
海南雞飯和咖哩薯仔飯也好吃👍
